LISTERIOSIS - AUSTRALIA: BACKGROUND
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon, 14 Oct 2002 07:52:55 +0200
From: <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON [edited]
<http://www.GideonOnline.com>

Background on listeriosis in Australia:
Year Cases
1991 44 (26 in Victoria)
1992 38
1993 53
1994 34
1995 65
1996 70
1997 73
1998 58 (30 in New South Wales)
1999 63
2000 67
2001 61
Disease rates during this period were 0.3/100 000 to 0.4/100 000.
Between 1980 and 1995, 2 foodborne outbreaks involving 13 patients (0
fatal) were reported.
